overview: >-
  The user initiated a request to fix numerous issues within a pull request,
  emphasizing critical Vercel deployment failures. The agent adopted a
  systematic approach, starting with a comprehensive review of code comments and
  CI logs to identify security vulnerabilities, functional bugs, and linting
  errors. Key decisions included replacing an insecure 'true' cookie with
  HMAC-signed sessions, implementing robust input validation for API routes, and
  enhancing PDF generation logic for accuracy.

  During the process, the agent encountered and resolved several
  deployment-specific challenges. This involved refactoring authentication to
  use the Web Crypto API for Edge Runtime compatibility, correcting a missing
  database URL in the Prisma schema, and updating Next.js to patch a critical
  security vulnerability. The update to Next.js subsequently necessitated a
  minor adjustment to the Prisma schema due to version 7 breaking changes.
  Ultimately, while all code-related issues were resolved, the final Vercel
  deployment failure was attributed to unconfigured environment variables on the
  Vercel platform, for which the agent provided clear guidance to the user.
